            "answer_text": "It cannot be converted. To plan synthesis one must first have a product: CsCl . Then find a method of synthesis, then a source of necessary materials. You would go to the sigmaAldrich catalog and find CsCl HMMM. Cs is found as the chloride in residual brines from a mineral carnallite a MgCl2.NaCl.5H2O after the sodium and magnesium salts are removed. It is probably also found in Great Salt Lake and Dead Sea waters. It can be SEPARATED from NaCl NOT converted from NaCl. ",
