            "answer_text": "Increase in pressure increases the coordination number and increase in temperature lowers the coordination number. For example: On increasing the temperature of CsCl structure coordination number decreases from  8 : 8 to 6 : 6 On subjecting the NaCl structure to high pressure, it will increase coordination number from 6: 6 to 8: 8. ",
